    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Endangered rainforest tree of eastern Australia. It was heavily logged in the 19th and 20th centuries and has not recovered. It fast growing and found on volcanic and alluvial soils. Although its common names include the words "beech" and "teak," it is actually neither.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
